This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society) because it discusses the use of crowdsourcing as a lower cost method for conducting biomedical systematic reviews. It also involves the design of a crowdsourcing task for information extraction, which can be seen as a social computing problem. 

The paper also relates to the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) because it involves the extraction of structured data from biomedical literature, which is a common task in information retrieval. 

Additionally, the paper touches on the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it discusses the use of natural language processing techniques to extract information from biomedical literature. 

The sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also relevant because the paper discusses the design of a crowdsourcing task and the importance of providing clear instructions to workers. 

Finally, the sub-category of cs.DL (Machine Learning) may also be relevant because the paper mentions the use of statistical meta-analysis, which is a common method in machine learning for aggregating data.
